Kylian Mbappe saved Paris Saint-Germain from a goalless situation at home in their first leg match of the Champions League match against Real Madrid on Tuesday. The 90 minutes of the game ended 0-0, as Lionel Messi missed a penalty in the 62nd minute.
Mbappe fired the ball past Real Madrid goalkeeper, Thibaut Courtois, to score the winning and only goal of the match four minutes into injury time, securing a narrow 1-0 victory for Paris Saint-Germain against.
 Real Madrid in the first leg of their last-16 tie on Tuesday.
Madrid goalkeeper, Thibaut Courtois, had saved Lionel Messi’s in the 62nd-minute to give the Spanish team a hope of having clean record in France in their first leg of the round of 16 stage of the Champions League, unfortunately, Mbappe hit the net for PSG.
PSG will be facing Madrid in Spain for the second leg and decider game for the quarter final of the League on March 9.
